startICAPServer

public boolean startICAPServer(String[] parameters)
starts the ICAPServer as an instance of ICAPServer.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters.
parameters[0] argument is always the method name,
parameters[1] argument is the ICAPServer port,
parameters[2] is the ICAPServer root directory,
parameters[3] argument is the ICAPServer timeout.
If only parameters[0] is submitted the parameters will be taken from the configuration xml document in XTTProperties.
If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.
See Also:
ICAPServer, XTTProperties

stopICAPServer

public boolean stopICAPServer(String[] parameters)
stops all/one ICAPServers and all it's threads.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters.
parameters[0] argument is always the method name, no additional parameters are requeired, the optional parameters[1] argument is the ICAPServer port of the ICAPServer to stop, if omitted all running servers are stopped.
If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.
See Also:
ICAPServer.closeSocket(String), ICAPServer.closeSockets()

See Also:
ICAPWorker.setOverrideReturnCode(int,String)

setServerOverrideResponse

public void setServerOverrideResponse(String[] parameters)
Overrides the HTTP parts of the response, mainly headers and body. Headers have to be added as lines of text. The Body as base64 encoded content. The number of chunks the body is to be devided into can be specified. The last chunk will be at most numchunks-1 bytes bigger than the rest. overrideType can be either req or res, default is taken from the original ICAP http headers.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters.
parameters[0] argument is always the method name,
parameters[1] the http header block,
parameters[2] the content of the response base64 encoded,
parameters[3] number of chunks for the body,
parameters[4] the override type either res or req.
If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.
See Also:
ICAPWorker.setOverrideReturnCode(int,String)
